subSubSection.paragraph:
Anal appendages black, superiors bluish-ochreous on middle, distal portion of inferiors chestnut-coloured. Superior pair stout, strongly downbent apically, at first sub-cylindrical, thence greatly compressed for the distal two-thirds of each, apices narrow and tapering in dorsal view, very broadly and somewhat irregularly rounded in side-view, each provided with a short interior sub-apical hook, directed obliquely backwards and downwards, followed by a blunt tubercle. Inferior appendages a trifle longer and much slenderer than the upper pair, thick at base, then a little divergent and finally incurved, each with a strong subapical tooth, but with the apices rounded (
fig. 13
). Length: abd. + app. 40.5, hw. 26 mm.
